description:
Timmorn attacks the resort that Jay and Alan are staying at, and Aquaman stops them from killing him. When Timmorn returns and a man dies, Aquaman kills Timmorn himself. Triton takes Timmorn's son and prepares him for revenge.

Sentinel and The Flash have come into battle against gigantic monster with Sentinel preparing to kill the monster only to be attacked by Aquaman who wants to speak with the monster himself. He then refers to it by its name, Timmorn revealing he knew it as a boy before letting it go when it promises to never return to land again. Aquaman then delivers a chest full of gold to Sentinel to use to cover the damage, and gives Joan a ancient necklace as a sign of respect for hers and Jay's fiftieth anniversary.

The next night the two couples go out for dinner with Alan voicing his distrust of Aquaman, with Jay and Joan defending the undersea hero. While Jay enjoys his anniversary Timmorn begins to return to the resort as Aquaman tends to some captured Dolphins.

The Flash then becomes angry at the monster for once again ruining his anniversary attacking it until being swatted away, with Sentinel being forced to aid a man having a heart attack while Joan saves Jay by scooting a power line into the pool the monster stands in making it angrier.

Aquaman then arrives and knocks the monster out, with Sentinel alerting him to the death of a civilian with the intention of one of them killing the monster, Aquaman then takes it out to sea asking him why he decided terrorizing people was now a game with him just saying it suddenly came to him before Aquaman kills him by using his hook into his brain. Triton then brings Timmorn's son to his father's body declaring Aquaman did it telling him he will show him how to gain his revenge.
name: Depths of Perception
Xena: Warrior Princess: The Orpheus Trilogy Conclusion

volume.name: Xena: Warrior Princess: The Orpheus Trilogy

description: Writer Mark Waid (KINGDOM COME) takes the reins for a 2-issue story pitting the JLA against its greatest challenge! As seemingly unrelated catastrophes spring up across the globe, only the JLA knows the cause. But can they thwart Dr. Julian September before his freak coincidences eliminate them?
name: Synchronicity

description: "How to Play With Fire" part 1! Back home in London, John Constantine is confronted by remarkable changes that have taken place in his absence. Among them: growing mistrust amongst his acquaintances, the terminal illness of an old friend, and the disappearance of Abaton.
name: Blowing On The Embers

description: Deadpool goes on his first assignment for Landau, Luckman and Lake
name: Win, Lose, or Draw Blood

description:
"Cataclysm" part 12, continued from NIGHTWING (1996-2009) #20. Batman uncovers a clue that may reveal the villainous Quakemaster's whereabouts. But can he and Nightwing find the villain before he hits Gotham with another earthquake?

[continued from Nightwing 20]

GCPD reviewed a videotape delivered to them claiming responsibility for the earthquake. The "Quakemaster" wanted $100million. Batman searched for Jolene Rellazzo and realized she'd been abducted. Gordon readied a fake ransom payment and Batman stowed away on the pick-up helicopter with hit. He gathered the mooks who'd picked it up, but their boss got away. Batman met with Robin and Nightwing to discuss the situation.

[continued in Huntress / Spoiler: Blunt Trauma]
name: Master of Destruction- Cataclysm, Part 12

description: With Batman still unheard from, the Joker's rampage moves toward a climax that can destroy Gotham City. As the homicidal clown and his allies prepare to strike with an oil-tanker-turned-super-weapon, only Jim Gordon and his thin blue line of Gotham cops stand in the way. "Duty" part 2.
name: Duty: Part Two of Two

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
Alpha Flight has come to America. Their mission: bring Logan back to Canada. Wolverine has a counter-offer; chances are Alpha Flight won't be too happy about it..

[Note: The events in this story are also depicted, from other perspectives, in the story in ALPHA FLIGHT Vol. 2 #9.]

The phone answering machine at the Xavier Institute records calls from Kurt Wagner, Margaret Stone of the Department of Education, and Jean Grey while the X-Men are out.

On the road to , is on his motorcycle, transporting Sauron, who is bound in a burlap sack, to drop him off with someone better equipped to handle the reptilian menace. Without warning, a jet swoops down above them, causing them to skid. picks Sauron up off the pavement and they continue down the road.

In , Rogue visits Dr. Agee, a scientist who claims to have “cured” his mutant sister. Dr. Agee takes a sample of Rogue’s DNA and she leaves.

At the Summers’ cabin outside , , Scott Summers and Jean Grey discuss his worries about her wearing her green costume. Jean explains it is to empower herself, and to exorcise the evil and fear it once represented.

In the woods, is soon confronted by Alpha Flight, who block the road. He exchanges a few words with them, then gets back on his bike and resumes his trip. Guardian flies after him and Sauron, forcing them to crash. retaliates, while Sauron tries to hop away to freedom, only to bump into Sasquatch and Murmur. battles the rest of Alpha flight as Rogue, returning from the city, flies overhead and witnesses the melee. She tells she will return with the X-Men.

The Canadian super-team corner at a service station, when Vindicator notices ’s claws are bone, not adamantium, putting lie to the perception Alpha Flight had that their jet’s sensors located by tracking his metal-laced skeleton. Suddenly, is decked by Sasquatch (at Murmur’s command). He leaps to his feet and the conflict resumes, just as the X-Men arrive. The two teams immediately face off against each other. Cannonball launches himself at Flex, but stops short when it’s apparent the Alphan doesn’t seek a fight. They instead talk.

The battle goes on with Storm disabling Vindicator, Maggott challenging Murmur, Rogue tackling Radius, and fighting the rest, until Cannonball shouts to get everyone’s attention. He’s learned from Flex that Alpha Flight’s mission is to apprehend for a murder Department H claimed he committed, but the X-Men know was with them at the time. Vindicator believes them, and her mistrust of their superiors at Department H grows. makes peace with his one-time teammates.

Back at the mansion, the phone recordings continue: Scott leaves a hesitant, troublesome message.
name: North & South

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Jackson King and Stormwatch are able to view into a parallel universe where Jack Hawksmoor is the Weatherman and ruling the most powerful gathering of superheroes on his planet. However, Jackson soon realizes that Jack Hawksmoor in that universe can view him as well.
name: Bleed: Part 1

description:
Tommy and Natt fought back against the S.A.S. soldiers, but only succeeded in pushing their enemies even further. They must find a way to even the odds before it not only costs them their lives, but Sean's as well! "Who Dares Wins" Part 4.

Gotham's mafia is picked apart as what was once a 'simple' hit against Tommy and Natt the Hat degenerates into even more death and despair.
name: Who Dares Wins, Part 4

deck: Comet's in trouble and it's up to Supergirl to help. While this is happening though, romance between Comet and Supergirl also starts to bloom, ending in a kiss.
description: Comet, the newest hero in Leesburg, is being chased by someone named Fracture.; In the meantime, the Kents try to help Sylvia Danvers adjust to being Supergirl's mother.
name: Through A Fractured Prism

description:
Kyle has been swept up into a future where the Green Lantern Corps is a criminal organization. Will he be able to clear his name and get back home?

Ok folks our story opens up with The green lantern corp fleeing from the legion of superheroes. They as we find out are the worst criminals the future has encountered in quite some time. The lanterns use there powers to kick some legion ass and make off with the loot. The legion kick themselves but when they hear of a lantern in custody they drop by the jail o get him. Kyle well behaved and pleading his case of some misunderstanding gets rescued by the legion and taken to their HQ. Once there he learns that the Green Lantern corp is a group of criminals. Whats worse is he finds out Time travel has been outlawed so he cant be sent back home and as if that wasn't bad enough THEY HAVE NO RECORDS OF HIS TIME AS GREEN LANTERN!

so Kyle is left in a bad place he has no legacy...all they have is Hal Jordan records....

Being the great guy he is he soldiers on and helps the legion locate the evil corp, along the way future flash xs first with him quite openly much to his flattery yes but dismay nonetheless. The corp attacks, knocks her out and while kyle's distracted they knock him unconscious and take them aboard their base. The leader of the corp confiscates Kyle's ring but it wont work for him and it vanishes from his finger.

In an alley on earth Ganthlet the last of the guardians calls the ring to him and gives it to a young dark haired woman called Cary Wren as she places the ring on her finger she transforms into a green lantern, complete with classic costume.
name: Future Shock, part 1

description: Lord Fanny's bizarre mystical heritage leads to a violent confrontation with King Mob's Invisibles cell, critically wounding one member and changing the balance of power within the grand conspiracy forever.
name: The Philadelphia Experiment
Slave of Heavens, Part 4: Inconvenience, Be Not Proud

description:
With the Resurrection Man presumed dead after last issue, this time we look back at a story before the events of RESURRECTION MAN #1 as Mitch dies for the first time at the hands of a serial killer called the Candy Man.

A man calling himself the Candyman threatens the city of Caryville and only one man can stop him: Resurrection Man!
name: Cold Blood

description:
(continued from The Batman Chronicles 12)
Nightwing and Robin met at the clocktower to see if Oracle was ok (it was the first time Barbara and Tim met face-to-face). No one had seen Batman, but he was ok - saving victims from rubble in the guise of a police officer. Dick and Tim checked out the destruction at Wayne Manor and the Cave. Tim rushed off to check on his father; Dick located Alfred and Harold.
(continued in Batman 554)
name: The Day After Judgement

description: When a galactic bounty hunter comes to town, he enlists the aid of Steel to help track down a potentially deadly creature. But it seems as if Steel's the only one who takes the threat seriously.
name: Quest

description:
The good Doc trashed on Sally Jesse Raphael?! It's true! In the late 1980s, Bart Simms' daughter has written a tell-all book about his exploits, and since she's hated him from birth, it's probably not going to be good for his reputation! As impostors emerge from the woodwork to claim his name as theirs, Tomorrow is faced with his final battle...the one for his legacy!

A tribute to Frank Miller.
name: The Tomorrow War, pt 1

description:
Overview

MOM#8 A Rocketman and Rocketgirl cover introduces the high-flying heroes, who appear in an intitled story drawn by Al Plastino from their St. John incarnation. This tale is taken from Zip-jet #1, February of 1952. Mr. Scarlet must find the antidote to the "Formula For Death", drawn by Bob Fujitani, and reprinted from Fawcett's Wow #62, January of 1948. The sexy woman of mystery this issue is Starr Flagg- Undercover Girl. She meets "The Doom Of Siva Dey", drawn by Ogden(Herbie) Whitney, in a story from Magazine Enterprises' Manhunt #9, June of 1948.There's cat-fights and bondage thrills in this story that features a villainess who was actually revived in AC's long-running Femforce comic. That stalwart of Sterling Comics, Captain Flash is back to meet "The Return Of The Mirror man", as rendered by Mike Sekowsky, from Captain Flash #2, March of 1955. The Owl and Owlgirl swoop out of the midnight skies to keep criminals in check in a tale torn from the pages of Dell's Crackajack Funnies, drawn by Frank Thomas sometime in 1942. Wild man Jack Cole illustrates an early Midnight story from Quality's Smash Comics, circa 1941, and "The Menace Of The Horror Weeds" threatens the beautiful Princess Taia and Ibis The Invincible in a story from Whiz Comics #150, October of 1952. No less than seven Golden Age features reproduced in sharp, crystal clarity. Color cover, interiors are black and white with graytones. 52-page standard comic book format.
name: The Return of the Mirror Man

description: A hair's-breadth escape from Japal leaves Carson Napier and Tarzan separated at a most dire moment. But as Carson continues to gather information on the bizarre new cult that has overtaken the city, Tarzan is free to round up allies. If only he hadn't escaped into the waiting claws and web of a ferocious Venusian spider!
name: The Loveking - Part 2 of 4

description: The second to last chapter of the epic Grasscutter story line! Usagi and Gen finally catch up to Jei, the demonic warrior. But can they defeat someone who now has both the powers of heaven and hell? Meanwhile, Tomoe and Noriyuki have trouble on both sides, as they are pursued by the assassins and end up in the hands of the general who once sought to overthrow the Geishu lord's father. Also, Priest Sanshobo investigates strange lights in the forest.
name: Grasscutter, Chapter 7: Usagi and Jei

description: The Challengers travel to Idaho to investigate a series of disappearances from a survivalist group.

Cameron is laid up in a hospital in a coma after a wall fell on her during a battle between the Teen Titans and some wannabe villains. While her friends sit and wait to see if she will be okay Knob tells of his first time working with her and their meeting with Klarion.
name: Better Days

description: People of the world help Wally West in his race against Kwyzz, a strange energy creature who came through the radio from another world and was Wally's childhood friend.
name: The Human Race Part 3 of 3

description: Impulse is all wet. No, really wet, as the freak snow storm that earlier hit Manchester meets the Spring thaw, resulting in a flood that pits the world's most reason-challenged young hero against something even more mindless than himself...the forces of nature.
name: Rising waters

description: Mr. Mind's plan for revenge shifts into high gear, forcing both Billy and Mary to cross legal lines in their desperate pursuit of answers. Torn by grief over the loss of their foster parents, the Captains are hard-pressed to keep their cool while their whole world crashes around them. "The Monster Society of Evil" part 2.
name: Monster Society of Evil: Part Two Requital

description:
Tim Drake makes his way to Ari's house to check on her but gets caught by the National Guard. He's told that most of the residents are staying in the high school because of reported gas leaks in the area. He decides to head off to their house where he finds his dad has hired workers to help fix their house. Little does Mr. Drake know that he has been scammed.

At night, Tim decides to go to the gym where survivors are staying as Robin and to check on Ariana again. He notices Stephanie Brown among the crowd and gets her attention. The two talk outside where she informs him that the Cluemaster is still at large. Steph convinces Robin to retrieve her costume from their house.

Robin quietly sneaks past the guards and into the Brown residence. As he searches inside, he stumbles upon Cluemaster who has the Spoiler costume. Soldiers quickly notice the light on and begin searching the house. A firefight ensues which gives Cluemaster an opportunity to escape. Robin gives chase through the rooftops.

The two fall on a covered pool where they confront each other. The National Guard pursue Cluemaster giving Robin a chance to escape. He decides to keep the costume for the time being. Tim returns his dad's deposit after finding the scammers the night before. The next day, he finds Ari by the driveway and the two decide to get back together.
name: Repercussions

description: Jack Knight seeks the help of the JLA as he embarks on an outer-space adventure! Committed to finding former Starman Will Payton, Jack must say good-bye to Opal City and prepare for his perilous journey to the stars. But that journey can't take place without a spacecraft...
name: Knight's Past

description:
Part 1 of the 3-part "Freeze Me with Your Kiss," the climax to TRANSMETROPOLITAN's first year. The cryogenically frozen head of Spider's ex-wife is stolen, his newspaper receives a threat on his life, and a mentally unstable police dog swears revenge on him. And that's only the beginning...

Strange things are happening to Spider. His wife's head has been stolen, three men tried to kill him, and he's on the run from the law for not having insurance. To make matters slightly worse, a headless child has shown up, claiming to be his son.
name: Freeze Me with Your Kiss, Part I of III

description: Jim Hammond leads the Heroes for Hire into the Master's trap! Also, has Thena joined the Heroes for Hire?
name: Rising Evil

description:
Ka-Zar brings together the forces of the Savage Land against the High Evolutionary. Shanna's 'cosmic' power is resolved.

Note: this comic is a special flip-book. With one part, the last issue of the original creative team, and a second part the start of the new creative team.
name: Revolution; The Savage

description: Quicksilver and the Knights of Wundagore discover something amiss with the High Evolutionary. What bizarre transformation has overcome Pietro’s most feared villain? Lord Anon stages a rescue for his fellow teammates.
name: Rescue Mission(s)!
Man of the People, Identity Crisis (Part 2)
Stuck In The Middle With You!

description:
This issue ends with more huge cliffhangers and never finishes them as this is the last issue of the series.
In the Story Captain Christopher Pike is shown up by Kaaj on the planet's surface and had his shuttle craft badly damaged with Spock, Phillip Boyce and Virka.  Number One is injured on the bridge with many others when her head it hit in a fall from a blast.  The whole crew is surrounded by Klingon ships and the first Captain of the Enterprise ever Robert April is in command.  The End.
name: Nemesis

description: Fire and water! The undersea adventure continues as the Voyager sinks even deeper into the depths of the ocean planet!
name: Part Three

description:
In the regular mainstream, Dr. Doom and Puppet master had transfered the minds of the Fantastic 4, Alicia Masters and Franklin Richards in the bodies of tiny robot clones of themselves without their powers. They are then placed in a town full of human like robots called Liddleton and they dont realize. When they do, they manage to escape, Thing who here is human considers staying so he is human and Alicia isnt blind. But soon decides to leave. But......

What if The Thing had refused to leave Liddleton?

The rest of the Fantastic 4 leave with Franklin, Thing and Alicia to themselves saying they'll return in a week. Franklin and Alicia believe this is the real world, so they believe they are house hunting. After weeks go by with no sign of the rest of the team. The Thing starts wondering what happened? Eventually he manages to return to being the Thing and realizes the rest of the team are dead. He heads back home where Puppetmaster had told Alicia and Franklin the truth. They fight off Dr. Doom and return to the normal world at Castle Doom.

Alicia being angry that Thing had lied to her, now sees what he truely is...a monster. Soon a giant Dr. Doom attacks the castle and reveals this was his plan all along and its revealed that they are in a tiny world version of Doom castle with them still not in their normal bodies. Now Thing, Alicia and Franklin are trapped their forever.
name: The Thing... Human again?

description:
Katchoo walks into a service station, with a bruised face, and as she picks up goods the clerk watches her intently, much to her disgust, she walks up to a drinks cabinet and kicks in the glass door and trashes the place.                                      
 
It's Francine's birthday and its not going as well as she would like. Her family light heartedly joke about the accident at the play but she is still embarrassed by it.
 
Katina's mother bails her out and the two argue. Her mother refuses to acknowledge that her new husband beat and raped Katina. Katina walks away from her mother and declares she has no home anymore.                                        
 
Fran zips up her jacket and covers herself up as much as possible. On entering class she gets an ovation and chants of  "Toga". Freddie is now suddenly very interested in Fran but she is still preoccupied. She finds a note in her locker saying Katchoo is leaving town tonight and would like to see her before she catches the bus. 
 
In the cold evening air the pair chat slowly. Francine baked Katchoo some cookies for the trip and and laments that she just found her best friend and now she's leaving. But theres nothing she can do.
name: Cowboys and Cowgirls

description: New York has become much too hot for the GEN13'ers, and not just because it's June. I.O. is moving in, so Lynch, Fairchild, and the others move out to the . Hey, if it's good enough for Hemingway, it's good enough for Grunge. But what they find waiting for them down there ain't exactly "The Old Man and the Sea". Are those drug runners? Are those voodoo drums? Are those zombies?!? Maybe, and then again, maybe not. Also, Alex Fairchild and the GEN13 gang are finally reunited; the first gust of the winds of change to come.
name: Stranger Than Fiction

description: Magnum Force Book 4 of 4: Love. The END of Quantum & Woody? The heroes trash their uniforms, tired of attracting bozos and losers and villainous types. They dissolve the partnership, and head to Paris as they make their way home. In Paris they find they can't easily leave the path they've started on, as they find themselves hunted by the police and thrown in jail after having defended themselves from their attackers, only to be bailed out by the LAST person either of them would expect to see, after with they reluctantly resume their heroic identities for one final showdown with Magnum and the deadly WarLocke!
name: Magnum Force The Final Round: Hate

description: The Vegas showgirl named Nevada fights for her life, her sanity and her ostrich Bolero in this genre-bending miniseries! When those about you are losing their heads, plus assorted limbs, keep dancing! Nevada tries, but it's not easy. Another dismembered corpse has surfaced--in the Nile Hotel's swimming pool. Rip is obsessed with a hieroglyphic virus in the casino's computer system. And Nevada herself is coming untethered in time. At least a decent-looking guy is trying to get her attention...but he'll have to wait in line behind the Las Vegas cops and Ogden Locke, who's turning out to be smarter than the average wino.
name: Nibbles

description: On Muir Island, Nightcrawler is approached by the demon lord Belasco
name: Unforgiven
Nowhere to Run, Nowhere to Hide

description: The Doom Patrol has acquired all of the amazing powers of the Justice League's original members. Can the DC Universe's strangest heroes stop the Brotherhood of Evil where the League failed?
name: Sum of Their Parts

person_credits.name: David Mack
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist

description: In revolution-torn Paris, Isadore Hibbert leads her comrades to La Grande Prison. As she nears the goal of the mission to which she has devoted her life, Isadore may have to choose between freeing her lover and freeing herself with the dark arts she's learned.
name: Part Three: Winter Into April
Finder

description: One month later - The world reels from the bomb at Monument Valley; Cassidy and Tulip are on the run; Starr is under the protection of the Chunt Brothers; Featherstone hunts for Starr.
name: Badlands

description:
Spawn's necroplasm mysteriously draws him into the "dead zone" where he is engulfed by The Heap.

Sam & Twitch encounter Cog in their office. Cog leaves them a dossier to help Spawn. Eddie Beckett, who found the bag of necroplasm left by the Freak, is stabbed in an alley. With the aid of the necroplasm, he morphs into the Heap, a ghoulish creature consisting of the rubbish mankind has discarded. As the heat in Manhattan climbs to 130 degrees, the angel Bootsy asks Cog to help Spawn. Meanwhile, Spawn encounters the Heap and is absorbed into the Heap's refuse body!
name: The Heap

description:
After killing Atlan, Triton attacks Poseidonis and kills the Cybernetic Entity; the city settles to the ocean floor, and then Triton kills Aquaman.

Triton has tracked down Atlan, killing the ancient sorcerer for his part in the birth of Aquaman. While back in Poseidonis rebuilding their life's in the city following it's use as a weapon against the Milenium Giant as Tempest addresses the people to the coming of the election for High Councillor, Vulko then challenges Aquaman's right to do this as Tempest passes out sensing Atlan's fate. Meanwhile Aquaman oversees the rebuilding of Nuada's people, before reaching out to Garth through the The Clear who lets him know the threat is heading towards the city and he is on his way with what little aid he can find.

Triton then arrives bringing Timmorn's son to Nuliajuk to bring out the young monster's full potential which she readily does. While back in the city Vulko and Dardan continue their plan to get Koryak elected to the High Councillor against Garth who they feel would be little different then the king with Koryak offering the solution of something happening to Garth. Garth then arrives to find Koryak to prepare for the immanent attack, but are unable to be ready when Triton arrives. Tempest then heads out to meet Triton as the city's first line of defense,but is easily defeated. While in the ocean two fish find Atlan's body managing to get it inside of his magical bag, with the last line's of defense proving ineffective. Fortunately Aquaman arrives riding a whale attacking the god while commanding the ship to move the city away. However it is prevented by Timmorn's newly mutated son attacking the city, killing the sentient entity which the city floats on.

Aquaman then enacts his plan as Triton talks Dolphin leaps from behind stealing his Triton, as he commands his army of sea creatures to attack.However Triton then reveals that it is merely a focal point before wiping out Aquaman's army with Dolphin being attacked by the monster as the Triton returns to Triton. As the city sinks back to the ocean floor, Aquaman calls for his fish army to regroup but is attack viciously by Triton with Aquaman challenging his refusal to kill him as cowardice before being stabbed through the chest.
name: Line of Succession
Xena: Warrior Princess and the Original Olympics

volume.name: Xena: Warrior Princess: And The Original Olympics

description:
Summary:

After Batman disappeared at the end of #18, the Justice League stand baffled as to what is going on, and what to do next. Martian Manhunter has a plan, to still apprehend Julian September, but when he asks Oracle for information, she is to busy to give any to him. Over hearing her thoughts of "two bullets and everything changed," Martian Manhunter believes Oracle has removed herself from the case to regain her legs. Martian Manhunter begins to fade, but as he does, he tells the rest of the JLA to fill in the Atom when he takes his place. After the Atom arrives, he is briefed, and begins to work on a way to restore the natural order of things.
name: Seven Soldiers of Probability

description: Gavin and Ellie are pulling strings, and Constantine's life has almost completely unraveled. With nowhere else to turn, John must make a last, desperate deal with a highly unlikely party. "How to Play With Fire" part 2.
name: Fanning The Flames

description: Ajax is killing all those who stand between him and Deadpool. He is close to achieving his final goal when he stumbles upon the cabin of Dr. Killebrew.
name: You Want Me to Do What?!

description:
A subway train full of commuters is trapped in a quake-damaged tunnel beyond any hope of rescue. Batman and Robin know a way to reach them. So does the Ratcatcher.

Batman and Robin begin work on clearing a boulder blocking access to the Rocket Tunnel. A small number of commuters are still trapped in the subway. Efforts to mount a rescue are stopped by an aftershock which has increased the risk of a collapse.

Meanwhile, having escaped from Blackgate Prison, Ratcatcher aims to release the city's sewer rats. Further ahead in the tunnel, Batman and Robin begin blasting through the walls in an attempt to rescue the trapped commuters. As they start the rescue, they run into the Ratcatcher.

Thousands of rats descend on the subway car responding to the Ratchatcher's call. Their combined weight causes it to shift and give way to the ceiling as the floor follows. The rats go down with the car and this leads to a confrontation between Batman and Ratcatcher.

Batman convinces Ratcatcher to show him the way out of the tunnels by removing his mask making him vulnerable to the cyanide gas he released during the fight. The commuters are successfully rescued as reported by Vesper Fairchild and Ratcatcher is taken back into custody.
name: Trapped Like Rats

description: "Stalking" part 1! The "Summer of Peace" in Gotham City is shattered when a killer targets the city! Terror grows as the killer displays no rhyme or reason in attack: everyone is a target. Can Batman stop the enigmatic murderer before another seemingly random victim falls?
name: Stalking: Part 1

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
Cyclops thinks it may be time to reassess Professor Xavier's dream and so he invites the X-Men to his new home in Alaska. But Scott has another motive for gathering his teammates: Jean Grey's recent interactions with the Phoenix Force may be spiraling out of control...

Bobby Drake, Warren Worthington and Hank McCoy are in a four-wheel drive taxi outside Anchorage, Alaska, heading toward Scott Summers' cabin to visit him and Jean Grey (and in response to Scott's troubling phone message about Jean). A crow hits the windshield, and the cabbie swerves, first hitting a moose, then crashing into totem pole. Chris Miller of the Anchorage Police (and a neighbor of Scott and Jean) soon arrives to assist. He euthanizes the moose, while Bobby catches a brief glimpse of a "strange guy", who abruptly vanishes. Miller then drives them to Scott's cabin.

Meanwhile, at the Xavier Instituite, Rogue flies toward the city, while Wolverine awaits G. W. Bridge of S.H.I.E.L.D. to finally take Karl Lykos (Sauron) off the X-Men's hands. Rather than meeting face-to-face, the agent merely teleports Lykos off the grounds.

In Alaska, the group arrives, and Bobby, Warren and Hank meet Miller's wife, Staci, and her sister Melissa. Soon, the X-Men are catching up with each other, but there is a tension, as Scott leaves his concerns about Jean unspoken. While Scott shows Hank to his room, Warren talks to Jean about his rocky relationship with Betsy. Upstairs, Scott shares with Hank his fears about Jean possibly coming under the influence of the Phoenix Force. During this time, crows gather outside and watch the house.

Later, the five discuss how to proceed with their search for Professor Charles Xavier. Jean says that though she's pushed her power to limits in a worldwide psychic search, she's found no trace of him. Then the room beings to fill with smoke, and they clear the chimney of what's blocking it. Warren flies to the roof to check, finding a dead crow, and while he's up there, he's spotted by Melissa who is out for a walk.

In New York City, Rogue spots Dr. Agee, whom she's seen about a cure, coming out of a genetics lab named "Mutopia". She confronts him, and he stammers that Mutopia is a group that tried to recruit him, but he declined.

Back in Anchorage, the X-Men are in town for dinner out. On the way, they encounter a protest by local Inuits, demanding the return of their ancestral lands. Bobby again sees his "strange guy", dressed in some sort of ritual garb, but again he disappears before the rest see him. Later, in the restaurant, Scott prepares to tell his teammates his ideas for a new direction for the X-Men. Outside, the crows ominously continue to gather
name: Reunion

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: As StormWatch watches events unfold on a parallel Earth, that worlds Jack Hawksmoor, the current leader of that worlds StormWatch, worried about an inevitable alien attack, sets out to recruit as many of the alternate Earths heroes as he can to forge a repelling army. Yet while some sign on, he is rebuffed by Battalion and Zealot. Finally, matters only get worse as Hawksmoor is forced to declare war on the United States Army, as they try to seize control of the alien pylon technology!
name: Bleed, Part. 2

description: In the conclusion to Garth Ennis' latest HITMAN arc, dissention among the ranks of the S.A.S. might give Tommy and Natt the opportunity they need as violence explodes in a vicious final showdown between the duo, the S.A.S. and Men's Room Louie's mob!
name: Who Dares Wins, Conclusion

description: The Rat Creatures, the Bones and their friends make their way down from the mountains, unaware they are being followed and eavesdropped upon by Roque Ja. As they descend, the Rat Creatures reveal that the current unrest has only come about since The Hooded One arrived, bringing with him the locusts and the strange dreams. At that moment, Roque Ja reveals himself to the party and orders them back up the mountain. Before they can go too far, the real Kingdok arrives and starts to fight with Roque Ja. The Bones use the opportunity to escape, fleeing from the scuffle and running down the mountain. Kingdok is felled. Roderick, the possum kids, and the orphans split up and leave. Bartleby rejoins the pack and the Rat Creatures carry the fallen Kingdok away.
name: Call of the Wild

description:
Future Shock continues as Kyle is trapped and taken hostage by the evil Green Lantern Corp. All this and a newly minted Green Lantern shows up to save the day! Is this the end of Kyle? Find out inside!

After the cliffhanger that was last issue we learn that the new GL a female named Cary wren is a descendant of kyle, thus why the ring works for her and our pal ganthet fills her in on everything else. Meanwhile Kyle is questioned by the leader of the lanterns about his disappearing ring. Oblivious kyle questions the authenticity of their claim to the green lantern name. Turns out each ring has a narrow range of abilities based on an energy siphon on board thanks to the location which is oan airspace.

Kyle thanks to training from Donna manages to escape but the legion members are still captive. Cary arrives to save them while the other set of legion members spring a surprise attack and a big fight plays out. we get xs and Cary together a bit right before kyle comes in and stops the siphon which causes the lanterns to be defeated.

Kyle doesn't get much time to socialize as he gets his ring back and brainiac 5 whisks him to when there should be green lanterns. The artpeice said to be one of history's greats is handed back to the museum and we get one of the most compelling shots, it was made by Kyle....entitled Sorrow.

We see kyle back in the past getting reoriented and he runs into......SINESTRO FIGHTING HAL!!!
name: Future Shock, part 2

description: On the run from King Mob in London, Dane receives a startling offer from Sir Miles and the Invisibles' enemies, and what happened during Dane's alien abduction is revealed.
name: Scorpio Rising
Slave of Heavens, Conclusion: When All Else Fails

description: Some of the greatest names in comics contribute to this remarkable 4-issue crime-anthology miniseries, featuring a shocking painted cover (with a partial overcover) by Tim Bradstreet. In "Clean House" (written by Brian Azzarello and painted by Tim Bradstreet), a mob informant's new life takes a deadly twist; in "The Bear" (written and illustrated by Dave Gibbons), white snow runs red as old scores are settled in New Russia; in "Your Special Day" (written by Doselle Young with art by Frank Quitely), a lonely hitman stages a suicidal hit at the wedding of a Mob Boss's daughter; and in "Chains" (written and painted by Peter Kuper), a line of white powder links lives--and fates--from the Golden Triangle to the Big Apple.
name: Clean House; Chains; Your Special Day; The Bear

description: Dick returned home. Tad had invented himself as Nite-Wing (oblivious to the real Nightwing) and was shot up on his first night out. When he heard that his apartment building had been condemned, Dick purchased it and scheduled a full renovation. Soames began learning to walk again. Roland Desmond (Blockbuster) contacted police chief Redhorn - they both sent people to the hospital to finish off (the incorrect) Nightwing.
name: False Starts

description: There's a fifty million dollar bounty out on the The Joker, and there's no shortage of people trying to claim it. The only place Batman can keep his nemesis safe is... the Batcave. But even that haven may not be safe enough when the Riddler comes calling.
name: With A Price On His Head!

description: Technet, alien bounty hunters, are hired an interdimensional goddess to kidnap Franklin. The purpose is to investigate his reality-altering powers but naturally, the Fantastic Four don't care.
name: April is the cruelest month

description: As the series concludes, Natasha Irons lies at death's door thanks to Skorpio. Worse yet, she's taken to the Garden State Medical Center, under the care of Dr. Sam Ellis, aka Skorpio!
name: Requiem

description: We continue Doc's final battle as he comes face-to-face with the people he's been dreading to meet — his creators from the future! Plus, more of Bart's grandson Jason as he comes one step closer to meeting his destiny.
name: The Tomorrow War, pt 2

description: Having found and befriended the forest-dwelling Timals, Tarzan has a plan to descend upon the Valley People and destroy their fields. . . fields of the Flowers of Forget, the pollen of which has the power to turn the strongest mind into a passive fool! And Carson of Venus isn't one to sit idly by, especially when the Myposans have captured all of the mythical Gerloogans, and are slowly dehydrating them to death!
name: The Loveking Part 3 of 4

description: Final Issue! Saxon, the man committed to destroying the Challengers, returns from death once again, and this time he's learned secrets that no human should ever know!
name: ... Your Time Is Up!

description: "The Black Flash: Part 1 - The Late Wally West." Wally talks to Jay Garrick about marrying Linda. Meanwhile, Max Mercury sees something disturbing and mysterious in a photo, and crazy weather conditions begin occurring all over.
name: The Black Flash Part 1 of 3

description: The Trickster is back in town. And you can bet he's got something up his sleeve when, working with Impulse, he tricks Manchester's rival crime families into believing the toxic waste they've been dumping in town is actually a formula that can turn metal into gold!
name: The Trickster

description:
Batman & Superman in "The Green Bullet"

There's been a grisly murder in Gotham, and the clues all point to a certain Man of Steel! A tale from the early days of the league.

The Silver Age JLA in "For Sale - The Justice League?"

When a tycoon donates a billion bucks to the Justice League, it's up to Green Arrow to prove that money can't buy justice!

Justice League International in "Mousebusters"

Booster Gold and Blue Beetle take on the mouse that "ambushed" Guy Gardner...and brother, it ain't pretty!

Red Tornado in "Tin Man's Lament"

One of the JLA's most mysterious members, the battered automaton known as Red Tornado searches for his lost humanity...and finds that he's still a hero!

JLA in "The Secret Society of Super-Villains"

One super-criminal's take of how the villains united when the new JLA was formed...and of the disastrous consequences!

Green Lantern & Martian Manhunter in "Warrior's Heritage"

Green Lantern Kyle Rayner learns a lesson in courage from the Martain Manhunter - then puts it to the test!

Aquaman & Wonder Woman in "Revelations"

It's Truth or Consequences from Aquaman and Wonder Woman when an undersea rescue yields unexpected secrets from the King of the Deep!en Lantern Kyle Rayner learns a lesson in courage from the Martain Manhunter - then puts it to the test!
name: The Green Bullet / For Sale - The Justice League / Mousebusters / Tin Man's Lament / The Secret Society of Super-Villians / Warrior's Heritage / Revelations

description: The Marvel Family pulls out all the stops as war is declared on the wretched worm, Mr. Mind! The globe-coveting grub's dastardly plan to commandeer America's Commander in Chief is thwarted, but that just makes the malevolent maggot even madder. "The Monster Society of Evil" part 3.
name: Monster Society of Evil Part 3: Fail Safe

description: The Monkey Cult is still working to kill all the world's top martial artists, as Batman and Green Arrow race back to Gotham City to team up with Nightwing and Robin. Meanwhile, a new monkey appears, the Paper Monkey, who is looking to take on just one martial artist in particular.
name: Brotherhood of the Fist, Part 3: Monkey Fist

description: Wesley Dodds has always considered his manservant Humphries to be his family, but Humphries has family of his own, and when a tragic fate threatens his closest relative, the quiet butler must become a detective in his own right.
name: The City Act III of IV

description:
In this "Times Past" story, the maniacal Prairie Witch returns, but this time, she crosses the bombastic Phantom Lady! Set in the Golden Age, Ted Knight and Phantom Lady join forces to stop her deadly crime spree. But are they strong enough to stop the Prairie Witch's cruel magicks?

Phantom Lady, the cousin of Ted Knight, travels to Opal City in order to find and capture the Praerie Witch, who pulled a robbery at a gala filled with wealthy people back in Washington before starting her crimewave in Opal. Together with Starman, she manages to defeat the Witch and reclaim her lost possessions, as well as the jewelry that has a million dollar reward posted for it, all of which is dedicated to war bonds.
name: "1943: Things That Go Bump in the Night"

description:
Following their defeat of the Master, the Heroes fight on two fronts to save the lives of Iron Fist and Jim Hammond! Plus, are Hercules and Iron Fist leaving the Heroes for Hire?

Having defeated the Master and escaping his space-bound Citadel, the Heroes for Hire plummet toward Earth in three escape pods. Cushioned from the hard impact of the landing by the pods' interiors, the team emerges unscathed, except for Danny Rand (Iron Fist) and Jim Hammond. In order to save Luke Cage's life, Fist had imparted his chi, or life energy, into Luke's body, leaving himself seemingly dead. The android Hammond was deactivated when it was discovered the Master had placed a controlling device within his artificial body. Black Knight and Thena go airborne to rush Danny to the headquarters of Oracle, Inc.

Later, in the medical lab, Dr. Jane Foster gives her diagnosis to Luke, Jennifer Walters (She-Hulk), Dane Whitman (Black Knight),Thena, Hercules and White Tiger. She can't find anything physically wrong with Danny, but says it's as if the life's gone out of him. Tiger expresses her anger toward Luke for having played a traitor in their recent adventure, but is held back by the others. Jen then has an idea and leaves to make phone call.

Dane turns his attention to Hammond, who lies inert in the lab where he can be examined. He devises a plan to have Ant-Man (Scott Lang) shrink down and enter the android's body to search for the control device, while Thena maintains psychic contact with him.

Back at the infirmary, Misty Knight and Colleen Wing have arrived to see Danny. Misty is heartbroken at the possibility of losing him. The group then hear drumbeats and witness the arrival of Jericho Drumm a.k.a. Brother Voodoo, summoned by Jen. He explains he can use his mystic skills to withdraw some life force from each of them to attempt to reignite the spark of life in Danny's body. He warns that the ritual has to be precise, as it could leave Danny dead, or it could kill them all. Luke, Misty, Colleen and Tiger agree to participate in the ritual.

At the lab, Ant-Man travels through Hammond's system, capturing what he sees on a video camera fed back to video screens which Dane monitors. Dane wonders at the near identical similarity of Hammond's body to that of the android Vision. Ant-Man finds the control device within Hammond's electronic brain, and using the tiny sparks that allow Hammond to become the Torch, destroys the unit. He then reemerges, briefly aflame, and Dane and Thena proceed to reactivate the android.

At the hospital, the ritual proves successful as Danny awakens. Seeing Misty embrace him, Tiger slinks away, feeling dejected.

Days later, Jen and Hammond discuss matter's at the latter's office. He expresses concern at the ease with which he had been contolled by the Master and doubts his humanity. Jen assures him she finds him "more human than most."

At the same time, the recovered Danny informs Luke he intends to take a short hiatus from Heroes for Hire. Before he departs, they take a moment to revel in their friendship.
name: Fallout!

description: Blind... Alone... And stalked by the Punisher!
name: Jungle Book

description: Attack of the Acolytes! Quicksilver ignites a feud with Exodus, following an attack from his terroristic band of mutants. In battle, Lord Anon crosses a line he has never crossed before.
name: ...Escape from the Savage Land!
